<br />
<br />That  should settle the NTSC/PAL problem.
<br />
<br />Anyways, if you're going to be building NES carts (as opposed to Famicom carts or emulator ROM's), keep in mind that you'll need to get your hands on 10NES chips so the lockout chip doesn't stop you in your tracks.  That is unless you plan to just use a hundred SMB/Duck Hunt carts to pop the ROM's onto.

		

